@startuml EventDriven
!theme plain

title Event-Driven Architecture — Message Flow

actor "External\nClient" as Client
participant "API\nGateway" as GW
participant "Order\nService" as OS
database "Order\nDB" as ODB
participant "Outbox\nRelay" as Relay
queue "Event\nBus" as EB
participant "Payment\nService" as PS
database "Payment\nDB" as PDB
participant "Inventory\nService" as IS
database "Inventory\nDB" as IDB
participant "Notification\nService" as NS
queue "Dead\nLetter" as DLQ

== Command (Synchronous) ==
Client -> GW : POST /orders
GW -> OS : Route request
OS -> OS : Validate + create Aggregate
OS -> ODB : INSERT order + outbox (TX)
OS --> GW : 201 Created
GW --> Client : OrderDto

== Event (Asynchronous, eventually) ==
Relay -> ODB : Poll outbox
ODB --> Relay : OrderCreated event
Relay -> EB : Publish OrderCreated

par Parallel Consumers
    EB -> PS : OrderCreated
    PS -> PDB : Process payment
    PS -> EB : publish PaymentProcessed

    EB -> IS : OrderCreated
    IS -> IDB : Reserve stock
    IS -> EB : publish StockReserved

    EB -> NS : OrderCreated
    NS -> NS : Send confirmation email
end

== Compensation (Saga) — Payment Fails ==
PS -> EB : publish PaymentFailed
EB -> OS : PaymentFailed
OS -> OS : Mark order cancelled
OS -> ODB : UPDATE status (TX + outbox)
EB -> IS : PaymentFailed
IS -> IDB : Release reserved stock

== Dead Letter Handling ==
PS -> EB : Nack (retry exhausted)
EB -> DLQ : Move message
DLQ -> Ops : Alert + manual review

note right of EB
  **Event Bus Guarantees**
  - At-least-once delivery
  - Topic/queue isolation
  - Publisher confirms
  - Consumer idempotency required
end note

note right of DLQ
  **DLQ Rules**
  - Max retries: 5 (exponential backoff)
  - Dead message retention: 14 days
  - Alert threshold: > 10 msgs / 5 min
end note

@enduml
